Ch 6. Data visualization

Initial setting

library(tidyverse)
library(ggplot2)
library(cowplot)
library(pander)
library(NHANES)
# drop duplicated IDs within the NHANES dataset
NHANES=NHANES %>% dplyr::distinct(ID,.keep_all=TRUE)
NHANES$isChild <- NHANES$Age<18
NHANES_adult=NHANES %>%
  drop_na(Height) %>%
  subset(subset=Age>=18)

try ggplot

NHANES_sample <- 
  NHANES_adult %>%
  drop_na(Weight, Gender) %>% #remove rows (individuals) with missing values for Weight and Gender
  sample_n(150) #take a random sample of n = 150 rows (individuals)
NHANES_sample %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = Height, y = Weight))

NHANES_sample %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = Height, y = Weight)) +
  geom_point()

NHANES_sample %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = Height, y = Weight, color = Gender)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm")
